Olufemi Olaniyi, Benin The governorship candidate of the All Progressives Congress in Edo State, Pastor Osagie Ize-Iyamu, has said he will soon announce his next line of action after the declaration of Governor Godwin Obaseki the winner of the Saturday poll. Ize-Iyamu, who trailed the winner with over 84,000 votes, said he was still studying the results  and he would make known his plan very soon. He said this on his Facebook page. It read, “I hereby thank and appreciate my teeming supporters, who have had to endure many evils including being prevented from exercising their franchise, for their support and determination during the election process. “I assure you all that I am studying the results along with other party members and will announce the next line of action soon. God bless you all.” Copyright PUNCH.
